main event: A witness in Dayton, Ohio observed a large, bright, fast-moving object in the sky on July 7, 1968 around 10:15 PM.
interesting points: The object moved rapidly to the southwest and then disappeared from view.
The witness, Theodore Dase, reported the sighting along with another witness, Joseph Schaffer.
Photographs of the object were reportedly attached to the report.
The report was sent to the Deputy Director for further investigation.
The object was described as a large, bright, fast-moving object.
